 :tx/rationale "ADR-BUDGET-007: Four Activation Strategies for Four k* Regimes. DECISION: The guidance system uses four discrete activation strategies (Signal < Imperative < Navigate < Demonstrate) calibrated to k* thresholds (0.2, 0.4, 0.7). Each strategy has a token budget ceiling that determines the maximum methodology injection cost. Signal (< 0.2): 5 tokens max — single keyword. Imperative (0.2-0.4): 20 tokens — one-line command. Navigate (0.4-0.7): 100 tokens — action + rationale. Demonstrate (>= 0.7): 300 tokens — full worked example. RATIONALE: Agents under context pressure need less ceremony, not more. The quadratic attention decay below k*=0.3 means every methodology token costs 4x its nominal value. ALTERNATIVES REJECTED: (a) Fixed token budget regardless of k* — fails under pressure. (b) Continuous scaling — harder to implement and test than discrete steps. (c) Binary on/off — loses too much information at intermediate k*. TRACES TO: SEED.md §8 (attention budget), INV-BUDGET-005 (command attention profiles)."
